OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dull and damp start to the
OL,6,Fday. However, it should become drier
OL,7,Fand brighter through the morning with
OL,8,Fa few sunny spells developing for the
OL,9,Fafternoon, these mostly to the east of
OL,10,Fhigh ground. It will feel warmer.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FRather cloudy with a few
OL,13,Fbreaks offering some bright or sunny
OL,14,Fspells to end the day. Often cloudy
OL,15,Fovernight with some patchy drizzle
OL,16,Fover the hills and mountains. Frost-
OL,17,Ffree.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
